---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Terms and Conditions - EZWin Academy">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Terms and Conditions</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg">
      <p class="mb-6">
        By accessing and using EZWin Academy's services, you agree to these
        terms and conditions.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
            1. Enrollment and Registration
          </h2>
          <p>
            Students must provide accurate information during registration.
            EZWin Academy reserves the right to verify all information provided.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Classes are conducted online via video conferencing.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Payment Terms</h2>
          <p>
            Fees are billed monthly and must be paid before the start of each
            billing cycle. Payment plans are available upon request and subject
            to approval.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Our money back guarantee applies during the first 4 weeks. If you do
            not see improvements and do not want to continue, WhatsApp us to
            request a refund. Approved refunds are processed within 7 to 14
            working days.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Except for the money back guarantee above, payment of all fees is
            strictly non-refundable and non-transferable. This applies under all
            circumstances, including but not limited to withdrawal,
            non-attendance, or changes in personal schedules, whether before or
            after the programme's commencement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Attendance and Conduct</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Attendance</strong> Regular attendance is expected. Students
            should join lessons on time and be prepared with the required materials.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Late Arrival</strong> If a student joins late, the lesson will
            still end at the scheduled time. No extension will be provided unless
            agreed by EZWin Academy.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Behaviour</strong> Students must maintain appropriate behaviour
            and show respect to teachers and other students. EZWin Academy reserves
            the right to remove a student from a lesson if disruptive behaviour occurs.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Damage / Misconduct</strong> EZWin Academy will take necessary
            precautions to safeguard the well-being of students. Any costs incurred
            as a result of damage, injury, loss, expense, or liability caused by
            the student to public and/or private property will be borne by the parents/guardians.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
            4. Class Cancellations and Make-Up Lessons
          </h2>
          <p>
            <strong>EZWin Academy Cancellations</strong> EZWin Academy reserves the
            right to cancel or reschedule classes due to unforeseen circumstances
            (e.g. teacher illness, emergencies). A replacement class or alternative
            arrangement will be provided.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Student Cancellations / Rescheduling</strong>
            Parents/guardians should inform EZWin Academy as early as possible if
            a student is unable to attend.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
            <li>
              Requests made at least 24 hours before the lesson may be eligible
              for rescheduling, subject to availability.
            </li>
            <li>
              Requests made less than 24 hours before the lesson, or no-shows,
              will be treated as a completed lesson and are not eligible for
              refund or replacement, unless due to emergency and approved by
              EZWin Academy.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Make-Up Lessons</strong> Make-up lessons are subject to scheduling
            availability and must be completed within a reasonable period determined
            by EZWin Academy.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Teacher Substitution</strong> EZWin Academy reserves the right
            to substitute or change teachers without prior notice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
            5. Class Schedule and Holidays
          </h2>
          <p>
            Lessons are conducted as scheduled, including during the MOE school
            holidays (March, June, September, November, and December), unless
            otherwise stated.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            If there are changes to schedules due to public holidays or special
            circumstances, parents/guardians will be informed in advance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. Lesson Recordings</h2>
          <p>
            All lessons are recorded by default.
            <p class="mt-4">
              By enrolling, parents/guardians consent to lesson recordings.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              If parents/guardians prefer a lesson not to be recorded, they must
              inform EZWin Academy in writing before the lesson begins. Approval
              is subject to EZWin Academy's discretion.
            </p>
          </p>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p>
              All course materials, including but not limited to notes,
              worksheets, and digital content, are the property of EZWin Academy
              and may not be reproduced or distributed without permission.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              EZWin Academy owns copyrights to students' work and compositions
              completed throughout the duration of the course. EZWin Academy may
              reproduce the work in a material form, publish and make an
              adaptation of the work for advertising or showcase purposes.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>
              EZWin Academy will provide educational services with reasonable
              care and professionalism. However:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
              <li>
                EZWin Academy does not guarantee specific outcomes, grades, or
                examination results.
              </li>
              <li>
                EZWin Academy shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
                special, or consequential losses (including loss of results or
                opportunities).
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
              9. Termination and Suspension
            </h2>
            <p>
              EZWin Academy reserves the right to suspend or terminate services
              immediately if:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
              <li>fees remain unpaid beyond the due date,</li>
              <li>
                the student or parent/guardian displays abusive behaviour,
                harassment, or misconduct,
              </li>
              <li>
                the student repeatedly disrupts lessons or refuses to cooperate
                with learning expectations,
              </li>
              <li>
                there is misuse or unauthorised sharing of EZWin Academy
                materials/recordings.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">In such cases, any paid fees are non-refundable.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
              10. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution
            </h2>
            <p>
              These terms and conditions are governed by the laws of Singapore.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              In the event of disputes, both parties agree to first attempt to
              resolve the matter amicably through discussion. If no resolution
              is reached, the dispute shall be subject to the exclusive
              jurisdiction of the Singapore courts.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">11. Privacy and Marketing</h2>
            <p>
              We collect and process personal information in accordance with our
              Privacy Policy. By using our services, you consent to such
              processing.
            </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Students and parents enrolled have given permission to EZWin
            Academy to use testimonials for advertising and marketing purposes.
          </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">12. Contact Information</h2>
            <p>
              The enrolling parent/guardian is required to notify EZWin Academy
              of any changes to their particulars as listed on the Registration
              form. All correspondence will be sent to the current email/mailing
              address and EZWin Academy accepts no responsibility for
              undelivered correspondence.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">13. Changes to Terms</h2>
            <p>
              EZWin Academy reserves the right to vary these terms and
              conditions without prior notice. Any changes will be updated on
              our website.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">14. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              For any questions regarding these terms, please contact us at
              support@ezwin.academy
            </p>
          </section>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .prose {
      color: #374151;
    }

    .prose h1,
    .prose h2 {
      color: #1f2937;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
